title: International House Price Database
description:
Quarterly house price index for selected countries beginning in first quarter 1975

The Globalization Institute of the Federal Reserve Bank of Dallas produces an international house price database. The data is updated and released quarterly.

Each dataset begins in first quarter 1975 and displays a house price index (HPI) for selected countries, which is selected to be "most consistent with the quarterly U.S. house price index for existing single-family houses produced by the Federal Housing Finance Agency." It also includes the house price index expressed in real terms (RHPI), the personal disposable income (PDI) index, and the personal disposable income expressed in real terms (RPDI) index. All variables in real terms are deflated with the personal consumption expenditure (PCE) deflator.

For detailed information on this dataset, including methodology, charts, links to external resources, FAQs, and contact information, see the source link below.

**Source:**  [https://www.dallasfed.org/institute/houseprice](https://www.dallasfed.org/institute/houseprice)

**Updated:** Not synced. This dataset is released quarterly by the Federal Reserve Bank of Dallas. If a quarter is not listed here, you may find it at the source link.
